HEADWORD: Stratagem
<hw>Strat"a*gem</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>stratag⟦egrave⟧me</ets> (cf. Sp. <ets>estratagema</ets>, It.
<ets>stratagemma</ets>), L. <ets>strategema</ets>, Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ to
be leader of an army, fr. <?/ a general; <?/ an army (probably as being
spread out; cf. <er>Stratum</er>) + <?/ to lead. See
<er>Agent</er>.]</ety> <def>An artifice or trick in war for deceiving
the enemy; hence, in general, artifice; deceptive device; secret plot;
evil machination.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fit for treasons, <qex>stratagems</qex>, and spoils.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Those oft are <qex>stratagems</qex> which error seem,⟦br⟧
Nor is it Homer nods, but we that dream.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stratagemical</ent>⟦br⟧
